money after the jury raised that question tuesday morning us 
district judge douglas woodlock again charged the jury on legal 
issues 
woodlock set a new trial july 11 a new jury will be chosen 
gerard indelicato who became the governors education adviser 
in march 1983 headed the states adult education program at the 
time the alleged scheme got under way 
he pleaded guilty last month to participating in the alleged 
scheme and testified against freedman he is to be sentenced july 
8 assistant us attorney ralph gants declined to say whether 
indelicato would testify in freedmans new trial 
indelicato won a recommendation from prosecutors for a reduced 
sentence in exchange for his cooperation in what gants called an 
ongoing investigation 
indelicato testified that the scheme involved skimming 80000 
from two adult education programs from 1979 to 1983 the money he 
testified was shared among freedman indelicato his brother 
joseph and a fourth conspirator antonio perrotta 
all but freedman have pleaded guilty 
prosecutors agreed to recommend to woodlock that indelicato 
receive a fiveyear prison term and pay an 80000 fine woodlock 
could exceed that if he chose 
indelicato became dukakis education adviser two months after 
