the commerce department reported tuesday that the trade deficit 
shrank more than 4 billion in march to 97 billion the lowest 
monthly deficit since march 1985 largely on a boom in exports 
the news was good for the dollar which surged against other 
major currencies tuesday the dollars longterm decline apparently 
has paid off by making us exports more attractive and currency 
dealers widely believe monetary authorities arent likely to 
