<TEXT>
enzo tortora a popular italian tv 
personality who was convicted of drug trafficking and organized 
crime charges but later cleared died wednesday of lung cancer he 
was 59 
tortora was the host of the weekly tv variety show 
portobello which regularly attracted an audience of 25 million 
after going on the air in 1977 
he was arrested in march 1983 after a criminal who turned 
states witness accused him of associating with the camorra the 
neapolitan version of the mafia in cocaine trafficking 
tortora was convicted in 1985 and sentenced to 10 years in 
prison the conviction was overturned the next year on appeal and 
upheld in 1987 by the nations highest court after he had been in 
and out of jail over a period of 1186 days 
tortora had maintained his innocence his case raised ethical 
questions about the use of suspectsturnedwitnesses whose 
testimony has led to major breakthroughs in mafiatype cases 
the small italian radical party took up tortoras defense and 
entered him as a candidate in elections to the european parliament 
in june 1984 he won a seat but abandoned it in 1985 to protest his 
conviction 
tortora who was divorced is survived by two daughters 
</TEXT>
