who supervised the appellate panels investigation 
doar also wrote the panels voluminous report accusing hastings 
of bribery conspiracy and obstruction of justice after a 3year 
investigation that he said involved 2800 documents and testimony 
from 110 witnesses 
the report was given to the house leadership in march 1987 by 
the judicial conference of the united states the chief 
policymaking body of the federal judiciary with the conclusion 
that consideration of impeachment may be warranted 
at the outset of todays hearing rep john conyers jr 
