natural hydrogen peroxide according to a report in thursdays 
issue of the british journal nature 
the rate of reaction was comparable to that expected from 
laboratory experiments they wrote 
the reaction produces sulfate which reacts with atmospheric 
moisture to form sulfuric acid a constituent of acid rain 
little sulfate was detected in the experiment which was 
performed in december 1985 but significant levels appeared when 
the experiment was done in springtime when more sun was available 
to promote sulfur dioxide reactions researchers wrote 
