<TEXT>
the consumer product safety commission issued 
a warning wednesday that small parts on an umbrella stroller may 
come out and choke small children who try to swallow them 
the 15000 potentially hazardous strollers were identified as 
model 1601 prt strollers that were sold between august 1986 and 
march 1987 at service merchandise stores 
the strollers are navy blue with red trim each stroller has 16 
tube end plugs that may dislodge and choke a small child who tries 
to swallow the plugs the cpsc said 
in addition when the plugs are removed the exposed metal 
tube ends could have sharp edges the commission said 
parents using the strollers should stop using them and 
immediately contact service merchandise for a modification kit 
it said 
the commission said it had received no reports of small children 
being injured as a result of the plugs or sharp edges but the 
nashvillebased service merchandise co is voluntarily offering the 
modification kits to customers at no charge 
to get the kit consumers should call 18002511389 tennessee 
residents should call 18002511212 
