a government investigating commission 
concluded wednesday that two sports organizations were remiss in 
the stadium stampede that killed more than 70 fans at a soccer 
match in katmandu on march 12 
many in the crowd that day accused officials of failing to open 
locked stadium doors and of failing to control the crowd when a 
sudden hailstorm caused spectators to panic 
the commission report listed the hailstorm as the main cause of 
the stampede but said the allnepal football soccer association 
and the national sports council failed to handle the incident 
properly 
the commission said preparations by the football association 
organizers of the match for exit routes from the downtown national 
stadium were not found to be satisfactory 
it said the sports council failed to keep stadium gates in a 
proper state during the match and that sports council security 
personnel failed to take appropriate actions during the emergency 
the stadium was nearly filled to capacity for the final game in 
a series between a national cigarette factory team and a squad from 
bangladesh 
spectators raced toward locked exit doors when the hailstorm 
burst with more than 70 people killed and about 100 injured in the 
stampede 
