association said that at least half of the postwar babyboomers 
are homeowners who have seen their family sizes and incomes 
increase in recent years at the same time home prices have risen 
sharply he noted 
therefore more people are making the decision that its a 
better value to stay put and remodel rather than move added 
brian patchan remodeling director of the homebuilders trade group 
homeowners are also finding lots of money available for 
remodeling through homeequity loans where rates are sometimes 
lower than those offered for conventional mortgages 
