april from yearearlier levels while total domestic production 
registered a 27 percent decline a trade association reported 
wednesday 
and the american petroleum institute said unlike previous 
months the latest domestic production figure did not include a 
yeartoyear increase in alaskan output to partially offset a 
decline in the lower 48 states 
in its monthly statistical report washingtonbased api said 
us imports of crude oil and petroleum products averaged 704 
million 42gallon barrels a day in april up from 577 million 
barrels daily in april 1987 
domestic crude production averaged an estimated 817 million 
barrels a day in april compared with 84 million barrels daily 
last april while deliveries of domestic refined products slipped 
by 01 percent it said 
