coleco industries inc which is 
struggling to stay afloat on wednesday reported it lost 474 
million in the first quarter 
the loss in the three months ended april 2 compared with an 89 
million shortfall in the same period of 1987 
sales plummeted to 737 million from 1245 million the toy 
manufacturer said 
coleco also announced it entered into an agreement with lenders 
under its recently expired banking agreements to provide immediate 
interim funding the company said it is continuing to negotiate 
with these and other lenders in order to provide additional capital 
for 1988 operations 
the company also said it will seek a buyer for several product 
lines including plastic wading and splasher pools steelwalled 
splasher pools and pool filters snow products childrens outdoor 
furniture and clubhouses and rideon and battery operated vehicles 
in 1987 these product lines generated gross sales of 77 
million the company said it does not plan to dispose of any other 
product lines 
coleco has slipped as its cabbage patch kids dolls declined in 
popularity over the last few years its problems were exacerbated 
by last years slump in the toy industry 
